'''Fehmi Mert Günok''' ({{IPA|tr|mæɾt ˈɡynok}}; born 1 March 1989) is a Turkish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

Günok started his youth career with a short spell in [[Kocaelispor]] and then joined Fenerbahçe in 2001, where he was eventually promoted to professional status and played at Süper Lig level, winning two league titles. He left Fenerbahçe in 2015 to join [[Bursaspor]], where he played for two seasons. In 2017, he signed for [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]], where he attained a third Süper Lig title in the [[2019–20 Süper Lig|2019–20 season]].

Günok represent Turkey at international competitions to date, starting from under-16 level in 2004, and made his senior international debut in 2012. He was the first-choice goalkeeper of the national team during the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group H|UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying stage]], in which they qualified for the [[UEFA Euro 2020|finals]], and was their starting goalkeeper at [[UEFA Euro 2024]]. He made a last-minute save to deny [[Christoph Baumgartner]] a goal in Turkey's match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]].

==Club career==
===Fenerbahçe===
Günok started his football career with a short spell at youth level football at [[Kocaelispor]] between 2000 and 2001, which he described as "playing in couple of games while my father was working there", while [[Mahir Günok|Mahir]], his father was employed as goalkeeping coach.<ref name="2011 TFF Interview">{{cite news |date=1 March 2011 |title=Fehmi Mert Günok: "Gelmek değil, kalmak önemli" |trans-title=Fehmi Mert Günok: "It's not about coming, it's about staying." |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=11920 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213213632/https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=11920 |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=13 December 2020 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=Tr}}</ref> Then, he was discovered by [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football team)|Fenerbahçe]] officials in 2001, in Istanbul, during a [[Artificial turf|small field game]] and, joined the team where his first football license was issued.<ref name="2011 TFF Interview"/> During his youth level career, he scored a goal from a penalty kick against [[Manisaspor]] in a [[U21 Ligi|PAF Ligi]] game, ended 2–0, on 9 March 2008.<ref name="2007-08 TFF PAF FB MAN">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe - Vestel Manisaspor TFF Match Details|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=66787|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|access-date=20 December 2020|language=En|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201220221019/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=66787|archive-date=20 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Mert Günok'13.JPG|left|thumb|150px|Günok in [[2013–14 Turkish Cup]] encounter against [[Fethiyespor]], on 4 December 2013<ref name="2013-14 TFF FB FET">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe AŞ - Fethiyespor Manisaspor TFF Match Details|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=128334|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|access-date=20 December 2020|language=En|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201220222705/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=128334|archive-date=20 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>]]
Günok signed his first professional contract before [[2009–10 Süper Lig|2009–10 season]].<ref name="2020 AA">{{cite news |date=23 July 2020 |title=Mert Günok, Medipol Başakşehir kalesine duvar ördü |trans-title=Mert Günok built a wall in Medipol Başakşehir's goal. |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/futbol/mert-gunok-medipol-basaksehir-kalesine-duvar-ordu/1919636 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213214328/https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/futbol/mert-gunok-medipol-basaksehir-kalesine-duvar-ordu/1919636 |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=13 December 2020 |publisher=[[Anadolu News Agency]] |language=Tr}}</ref> He was the third-choice goalkeeper, behind [[Volkan Demirel]] and [[Volkan Babacan]] of Fenerbahçe at [[2010–11 Süper Lig|2010–11 season]].

Günok made his Süper Lig debut against [[Antalyaspor]] on 15 August 2010, coming on as a substitute after Volkan Demirel got injured at the beginning of the second half, earning a clean sheet.<ref name="2010-11 TFF FB ANT ">{{cite news|title=Fenerbaçe - Medical Park Antalyaspor TFF Maç Detayı|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86903|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|date=15 August 2010|access-date=14 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201214114230/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86903|archive-date=14 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Günok maintained his place in starting line-up in the following two Süper Lig encounters, respectively against  [[Trabzonspor]]<ref name="2010-11 TFF TS FB">{{cite news |date=23 August 2010 |title=Trabzonspor - Fenerbaçe TFF Maç Detayı |trans-title=Trabzonspor - Fenerbahçe TFF Match Details |url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86917 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201214114700/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86917 |archive-date=14 December 2020 |access-date=14 December 2020 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=Tr}}</ref> and Manisaspor,<ref name="2010-11 TFF FD MAN">{{cite news|title=Fenerbaçe - Manisaspor TFF Maç Detayı|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86924|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|date=23 August 2010|access-date=14 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120914084657/http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=86924|archive-date=14 September 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> where he conceded five goals in total. During the home game against Trabzonspor, ended in a 3–2 loss, He saved the penalty shot of Argentine midfielder [[Gustavo Colman]].<ref name="2010-11 w2 TRA FEN">{{cite news|title=Penaltı avcısı Mert|url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/penalti-avcisi-mert-1644266|publisher=[[Milliyet]]|date=23 April 2020|access-date=10 April 2021|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210410212344/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/penalti-avcisi-mert-1644266|archive-date=10 April 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

Günok was given a chance in starting line-up at mid-season exhibition match against Belgian side [[K.R.C. Genk]], on 9 January 2013.<ref name="2013 Genk Game">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe 1-1 KRC Genk|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/fenerbahce-1-1-krc-genk-22319695|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=9 January 2013|access-date=14 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201214113253/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/|archive-date=14 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Due to Volkan Demirel's penal absence, Günok was featured in starting line-up of [[2013 Turkish Super Cup]] against [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray S.K.]] and chosen "man of the match",<ref name="2013 TSC MOTM">{{cite news |date=12 August 2013 |title=Maçın adamı Mert! |trans-title=Man of the match: Mert! |url=https://www.sozcu.com.tr/2013/spor/macin-adami-mert-352660/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201219173148/https://www.sozcu.com.tr/2013/spor/macin-adami-mert-352660/ |archive-date=19 December 2020 |access-date=19 December 2020 |publisher=[[Sözcü]] |language=Tr}}</ref> although Fenerbahçe lost by 0–1 final score after extra time.<ref name="2013 TSC">{{cite news |title=Galatasaray AŞ - Fenerbahçe AŞ - TFF Maç Detayı |trans-title=Galatasaray AŞ - Fenerbahçe AŞ - TFF Match Details |url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageID=29&macId=118760 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201219172832/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageID=29&macId=118760 |archive-date=19 December 2020 |access-date=19 December 2020 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=Tr}}</ref>

In [[2014–15 Süper Lig|2014–15 season]], Günok played three back-to-back Süper Lig games in September, respectively against [[Karabükspor]], Trabzonspor and [[Gaziantepspor]], and he saved 8 out of 10 attempts made by opponents in these encounters, during Volkan Demirel's penal absence.<ref name="2014-15 performance">{{cite news |date=24 September 2014 |title=Mert Günok Kaleyi Devrediyor |trans-title=Mert Günok is handing over the goal. |url=https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/mert-gunok-kaleyi-devrediyor-122753 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201219165258/https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/haber/mert-gunok-kaleyi-devrediyor-122753 |archive-date=19 December 2020 |access-date=19 December 2020 |publisher=[[Cumhuriyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref> After 14 years spent at the club, Günok, at the age of 26, was released by Fenerbahçe, on 15 June 2015.<ref name="2015 Fenerbahce release">{{cite news|title=Fenerbahçe, Mert Günok'u serbest bıraktı!|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/fenerbahce-mert-gunoku-serbest-birakti-29283200|agency=|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=15 June 2015|access-date=12 April 2021|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20210411211017/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/arsenal-sheffield-unitedi-3-golle-maglup-etti-41785968|archive-date=11 April 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> During his last season, he played in nine Süper Lig and nine Turkish Cup encounters, conceded 19 goals in total.<ref name="2015 Fenerbahce release"/>

===Bursaspor===
After being released by Fenerbahçe at the end of 2014–15 season,<ref name="2015 Fenerbahce Release">{{cite news |date=14 June 2015 |title=Fenerbahçe, Mert Günok'u serbest bıraktı! |trans-title=Fenerbahçe released Mert Günok! |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/fenerbahce-mert-gunoku-serbest-birakti |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213214553/https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/fenerbahce-mert-gunoku-serbest-birakti |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=13 December 2020 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref> Günok joined [[Bursaspor]], on a 3-season-long contract, on 22 June 2015.<ref name="2015 Bursaspor transfer">{{cite news|title=Mert Günok, Bursaspor'da|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/mert-gunok-bursasporda-29351875|agency=[[Anadolu News Agency]]|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=22 June 2015|access-date=13 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213215211/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/|archive-date=13 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> His contract was of €1.2 million salary per annum.<ref name="Bursaspor quit (2)">{{cite news |date=26 July 2017 |title=Mert Günok Galatasaray'a gidiyor! |trans-title=Mert Günok is going to Galatasaray! |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/mert-gunok-galatasaraya-gidiyor-40531562 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201220120152/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ |archive-date=20 December 2020 |access-date=20 December 2020 |publisher=[[Hürriyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref> Chosen as first-choice goalkeeper in the first half of the [[2015–16 Süper Lig|2015–16 season]], Günok was replaced by [[Harun Tekin (footballer)|Harun Tekin]] from February on by decision of manager [[Hamza Hamzaoğlu]], as he conceded 32 goals in 19 league games.<ref name="2015–16 performance">{{cite news|title=Mert Günok kesik yedi|url=https://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2016/02/08/mert-gunok-kesik-yedi-1454969287|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=8 February 2016|access-date=19 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201219170743/https://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2016/02/08/mert-gunok-kesik-yedi-1454969287|archive-date=19 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In his second season at Bursaspor, he was deployed only in Turkish Cup encounters. At the end of season, his contract was cancelled in return of his outstanding wages from Bursaspor.<ref name="Bursaspor quit (1)">{{cite news |date=25 July 2017 |title=Mert Günok Galatasaray yolunda |trans-title=Mert Günok is on his way to Galatasaray. |url=https://www.haberturk.com/spor/futbol/haber/1575717-mert-gunok-galatasaray-yolunda-galatasaray-transfer-haberleri |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201220120806/https://www.haberturk.com/spor/futbol/haber/1575717-mert-gunok-galatasaray-yolunda-galatasaray-transfer-haberleri |archive-date=20 December 2020 |access-date=20 December 2020 |publisher=[[Hürriyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref><ref name="Bursaspor quit (2)"/>

===Başakşehir===

On 31 July 2017, Günok joined [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.]]<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-10-15 |title=Son dakika... Başakşehir Mert Günok'u transfer etti - Spor Haberleri |trans-title=Breaking news... Başakşehir signed Mert Günok - Sports News |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/basaksehir-mert-gunoku-transfer-etti-664190 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213215436/https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/basaksehir-mert-gunoku-transfer-etti |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=CNN TÜRK |language=tr}}</ref> In his first season at Başakşehir, he was the second goalkeeper behind Volkan Babacan, his former teammate from Fenerbahçe, and deployed only at [[2017–18 Turkish Cup|Turkish Cup]] games and [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].

He made his debut at Başakşehir on 30 November 2017, against [[Kahramanmaraşspor]], at the fifth round game of Turkish Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kipaş Kahramanmaraşspor - Medipol Başakşehir FK - TFF Match Details |url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=192746 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201214163751/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=192746 |archive-date=14 December 2020 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref> Putting an improved individual display in pre-season trainings, he was given the starting line-up status by team manager [[Abdullah Avcı]] from [[2018–19 Süper Lig|2018–19 season]] on.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mert Günok’un kaleyi bırakmaya niyeti yok |trans-title=Mert Günok has no intention of relinquishing the goal. |url=https://www.fotomac.com.tr/basaksehir/2018/09/19/mert-gunokun-kaleyi-birakmaya-niyeti-yok |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201214164908/https://www.fotomac.com.tr/medipol-basaksehir/2018/09/19/mert-gunokun-kaleyi-birakmaya-niyeti-yok |archive-date=14 December 2020 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=Fotomaç |language=tr}}</ref> His first Süper Lig game with Başakşehir was against Trabzonspor, ended 2–0 for Başakşehir, at [[Fatih Terim Stadium]], on 12 August 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Medipol Başakşehir - Trabzonspor - TFF Match Details |url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=194515 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210410215751/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=194515 |archive-date=10 April 2021 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref> Günok saved a penalty against Konyaspor on week 7 encounter of [[2020–21 Süper Lig|2020–21 season]], eventually ended 2–1 for Başakşehir's favour, on 1 November 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-11-01 |title=Mert Günok penaltıyı kurtarmasaydı... |trans-title=If Mert Günok hadn't saved the penalty... |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/mert-gunok-penaltiyi-kurtarmasaydi-1582913 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210410211220/https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/mert-gunok-penaltiyi-kurtarmasaydi |archive-date=10 April 2021 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=CNN TÜRK |language=tr}}</ref> He missed 5 league games and was replaced by Volkan Babacan in December at 2020–21 season due to [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] quarantine.<ref>{{Cite web |last=İHA |date=2021-01-03 |title=Başakşehir savunması çöktü! Kabus gibi tablo... |trans-title=Başakşehir's defense collapsed! A nightmarish situation... |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/basaksehir-savunmasi-coktu-kabus-gibi-tablo-41704993 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210401125905/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/son-dakika-galatasaraydan-fenerbahceye-1959-oncesi-sampiyonluk-cevabi-41777568 |archive-date=1 April 2021 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref> Played as starter, he lost the [[2020 Turkish Super Cup]] up against Trabzonspor, played on a postponed schedule due to COVID-19 pandemic, ended in a 2–1 loss, on 27 January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-01-28 |title=Süper Kupa Trabzonspor'un! (ÖZET) Başakşehir - Trabzonspor maç sonucu: 1-2 - Fanatik Gazetesi Futbol Haberleri - Spor |trans-title=The Super Cup is Trabzonspor's! (SUMMARY) Başakşehir - Trabzonspor match result: 1-2 - Fanatik Newspaper Football News - Sports. |url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/futbol/super-kupa-trabzonsporun-ozet-basaksehir-trabzonspor-mac-sonucu-1-2-2197753 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210127213509/https://www.fanatik.com.tr/super-kupa-trabzonsporun-ozet-basaksehir-trabzonspor-mac-sonucu-1-2-2197753 |archive-date=27 January 2021 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=Fanatik |language=tr}}</ref> Günok was released by club on 15 August 2021 in return of outstanding receivables of Günok.<ref>{{Cite web |last=NTVSpor |date=2021-08-15 |title=Mert Günok Beşiktaş'ta {{!}} NTVSpor |trans-title=Mert Günok at Beşiktaş |url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/mert-gunok-besiktasta-6118e654c6598c171cb2f16b |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210830211056/https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/mert-gunok-besiktas-ta-6118e654c6598c171cb2f16b |archive-date=30 August 2021 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=NTVSpor.net |language=tr}}</ref>

===Beşiktaş===
Günok joined [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] on a three-year contract, as the seventh transfer of the club during the transfer window, on 15 August 2021.<ref name="2021-22 Besiktas arrival">{{cite news|author=|title=Last Minute: Beşiktaş signed Mert Günok in with a 3 years-long contract|trans-title=Son Dakika: Beşiktaş, Mert Günok ile 3 yıllık sözleşme imzaladı - Transfer haberleri|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/son-dakika-besiktas-mert-gunok-ile-3-yillik-sozlesme-imzaladi-transfer-haberleri-41873443|agency=|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=15 August 2021|accessdate=30 August 2021|language=Tr|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20210830211542/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/son-dakika-besiktasta-sergen-yalcin-kariyer-hedefini-acikladi-avrupa-hedefim-var-teklif-41884177|archivedate=30 August 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 September 2021, he made his debut with the team as a starter in a 3-2 away [[Süper Lig]] win against [[Antalyaspor]]. On 24 October 2021, he made his continental debut as a starter with Beşiktaş in [[UEFA Champions League]] match against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].

On 31 July 2023, Günok signed a new two-year contract with Beşiktaş, keeping him at the club until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=CNN Türk|title=Mert Günok'tan 2 yıllık imza |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/spor/futbol/mert-gunoktan-2-yillik-imza-2030069 |access-date=2023-09-29|website=www.cnnturk.com|date=31 July 2023 }}</ref> On 17 January 2025, Günok had signed a new 2+1 year contract with Beşiktaş, keeping him at the club until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 January 2025 |title=Beşiktaş'tan Mert Günok'a 2+1 yıllık sözleşme |trans-title=2+1 year contract from Beşiktaş to Mert Günok. |url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/sporskor/besiktastanmert-gunoka-21-yillik-sozlesme,TlCtoMtYY02Ny__ygEC0kw |access-date=2025-01-17 |website=www.ntvspor.com.tr |publisher=ntvspor}}</ref>

===Return to Fenerbahçe===
On 8 January 2026, he re-joined Fenerbahçe, signing a contract until the end of 2027–28 season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Yuvana hoş geldin Mert Günok
 |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2026/1/ailemize-hos-geldin-mert-gunok |date=8 January 2026 |access-date=8 January 2026 |website=Fenerbahce.org |language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Fehmi Mert Günok euro2020.jpg|right|thumb|175px|Günok at press-conference with Turkey in 2019]]
Substitited in 62nd minute following the injury of starter [[Cenk Gönen]], Günok earned his first senior cap during a friendly game against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] on 25 May 2012, ended 3–1 to Turkey, held at [[Red Bull Arena (Salzburg)|Red Bull Arena]], Salzburg, Austria.<ref name="2012 TUR GEO">{{cite news|title=Türkiye - Georgia Match Details TFF|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=106281|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|date=25 May 2012|accessdate=1 April 2021|language=Tr|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20210401185355/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=528&macId=106281|archivedate=1 April 2021|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 8 June 2019, he kept a clean sheet against defending world champions [[France national football team|France]] in a 2–0 win at a [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group H|Group H]] encounter during the [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] stage.<ref name="2020 Qualifiers France home ">{{cite news|author=|title=Turkey - France Statistics European Qualifiers UEFA.com|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2026087--turkey-vs-france/statistics/?iv=true|publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=8 June 2019|accessdate=7 August 2020|language=En|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200807123606/https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2026087--turkey-vs-france/statistics/?iv=true|archivedate=7 August 2020|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref> Conceding 3 goals in 10 games, Günok was the main choice goalkeeper of Turkey, which put their best defensive performance ever at qualifying phases of UEFA European Championship, under management of [[Şenol Güneş]].<ref name="EURO 2020 Gunes">{{cite news |last= |author= |first= |date=15 November 2019 |title=Şenol Güneş, Milli Takım'da tarihe geçti! |trans-title=Şenol Güneş made history with the National Team! |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/senol-gunes-milli-takimda-tarihe-gecti-41374846 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200717165405/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/senol-gunes-milli-takimda-tarihe-gecti-41374846 |archivedate=17 July 2020 |accessdate=17 July 2020 |work= |publisher=[[Hürriyet]] |location= |page= |pages= |language=Tr |format= |id= |quote= |agency= |authorlink=}}</ref><ref name="EURO 2020 Qualifying stats">{{cite news|title=Tarihinin en iyi performansı! Milli Takım...|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/tarihinin-en-iyi-performansi-milli-takim-41376957|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Hürriyet]]|date=18 November 2019|accessdate=13 August 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20200813160354/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/tarihinin-en-iyi-performansi-milli-takim-41376957|archivedate=13 August 2020|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref> He was called-up for the extended 30-men-squad ahead of [[UEFA Euro 2020]] by Şenol Güneş, announced on 14 May 2021.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]]|url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=628&ftxtID=35106|title=A Millî Takım'ın kamp kadrosu açıklandı|trans-title=National team training camp squad is announced|language=tr|date=14 May 2021}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=Turkish Football Federation |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> In their [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage|round of 16]] match against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] on 2 July, he made a crucial save, diving to his right to stop a header by [[Christoph Baumgartner]] in stoppage time, securing his country's 2–1 victory and qualification to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036204--austria-vs-turkiye/ |title=Austria 1–2 Türkiye |publisher=UEFA |date=2 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cglkxz50memo|title='Banks replica' - was this 'one of great saves in Euros history'?|date=3 July 2024|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=3 July 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Mert Günok was born in 1989 in [[Karabük]], Turkey, while his father [[Mahir Günok]]<ref name="Father">{{cite news|title=Fenerli yıldızın acı kaybı!|url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/fenerli-yildizin-aci-kaybi-1607701|publisher=[[Milliyet]]|date=6 October 2012|access-date=13 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213201502/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/fenerli-yildizin-aci-kaybi-1607701|archive-date=13 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> was playing at [[Karabükspor]]. His mother Necmiye died in 2011, following an undisclosed disease.<ref name="Mother">{{cite news |date=24 February 2011 |title=Mert Günok'un annesi vefat etti |trans-title=Mert Günok's mother passed away. |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/mert-gunok-un-annesi-vefat-etti-17105985 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213204531/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/mert-gunok-un-annesi-vefat-etti-17105985 |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=13 December 2020 |publisher=[[Hürriyet]] |language=Tr |agency=[[İhlas News Agency]]}}</ref>

Günok married Aslı Günok ([[née]]: Dalgalıdere) in Bursa, in 2015.<ref name="Marital status 1">{{cite news|title=Bekarlardan evliliğe 'Amin'|url=https://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2015/12/31/bekarlardan-evlilige-amin|publisher=[[Sabah (newspaper)|Sabah]]|date=31 December 2015|access-date=13 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213203237/https://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2015/12/31/bekarlardan-evlilige-amin|archive-date=13 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Marital status 2">{{cite news|title=Mert-Aslı Günok'un bebek alışverişi|url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/cadde/mert-asli-gunokun-bebek-alisverisi-2757662|publisher=[[Milliyet]]|date=10 October 2018|access-date=13 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213203433/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/cadde/mert-asli-gunokun-bebek-alisverisi-2757662|archive-date=13 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The couple welcomed their first child, named Alâ, in 2019.<ref name="Child">{{cite news|title=Paris Panteri Mert Günok'un büyük sırrı|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/paris-panteri-mert-gunokun-buyuk-sirri-41351491|publisher=[[Milliyet]]|date=16 October 2019|access-date=13 December 2020|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213204153/https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/|archive-date=13 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2020, he donated 100 pairs of goalkeeper gloves to 100 schools across Turkey.<ref name="Philantrophy">{{cite news |date=23 April 2020 |title=Mert Günok'tan 100 okula ikişer çift eldiven |trans-title=Mert Günok donated two pairs of gloves to 100 schools each. |url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/mert-gunoktan-100-okula-ikiser-cift-eldiven-6196637 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201213204910/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/mert-gunoktan-100-okula-ikiser-cift-eldiven-6196637 |archive-date=13 December 2020 |access-date=13 December 2020 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref>

